<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="632" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[2051,2644,2188,2618]" pageId="33" pageNumber="632">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1903" box="[2056,2241,2273,2302]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="33" pageNumber="632" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="agag">Gerbillus agag</taxonomicName>
is in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[2527,2638,2273,2302]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="33" pageNumber="632" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Gerbillus</taxonomicName>
. For some authors, such as D. C. D. Hap-pold in 2013, the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1903" box="[2405,2508,2347,2381]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="33" pageNumber="632" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="agag">G. agag</taxonomicName>
is a syno-nym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dollman" authorityYear="1914" box="[2164,2289,2390,2419]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="33" pageNumber="632" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cosensi">G. cosensi</taxonomicName>
; for some others, including F. Petter in 1975, G. G.Musser and M. D. Carleton in 2005, and A. Monadjem and colleagues in 2015, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dollman" authorityYear="1914" box="[2405,2532,2513,2538]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="33" pageNumber="632" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cosensi">G. cosensi</taxonomicName>
is synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1903" box="[2164,2264,2544,2578]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="33" pageNumber="632" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="agag">G. agag</taxonomicName>
. The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1903" box="[2440,2542,2544,2578]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="33" pageNumber="632" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="agag">G. agag</taxonomicName>
is here retained as valid pending further studies.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[1434,2644,2621,3480]" pageId="33" pageNumber="632">
D. M. Lay in 1983 considered that both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1903" box="[2011,2112,2621,2655]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="33" pageNumber="632" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="agag">G. agag</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dollman" authorityYear="1914" box="[2185,2310,2621,2655]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="33" pageNumber="632" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cosensi">G. cosensi</taxonomicName>
are valid. There are no genetic data. Moreover, D. Kock in 1978 recognized four additional subspecies: maradius, migeniae, 
<taxonomicName box="[1626,1744,2700,2734]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="33" pageNumber="632" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rosalinda">rosalinda</taxonomicName>
, and sudanensis. Subspecies 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas &amp; Hinton" authorityYear="1920" box="[2140,2239,2700,2734]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="33" pageNumber="632" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigeriae">nigeriae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[2308,2426,2700,2734]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="33" pageNumber="632" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rosalinda">rosalinda</taxonomicName>
have now been accorded species rank, but a thorough revision of this group is still needed. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
