<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="632" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="33.[1434,2644,2621,3480]" pageId="33" pageNumber="632">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1437,1685,3024,3049]" pageId="33" pageNumber="632">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 90-135 mm, tail 100-143 mm, ear 13-20 mm, hindfoot 25-30 mm; weight 30-34 g. This is quite a large gerbil of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[2432,2543,3055,3089]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="33" pageNumber="632" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Gerbillus</taxonomicName>
. It has hairy hindfeet soles and a long (125% of head-body length) tail.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
